parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, compromising the safety of the vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbag warning light on the dashboard
airbag failure to deploy in the event of a crash
collision without airbag deployment
injuries sustained due to lack of airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning airbag sensor can prevent the airbag from deploying in the event of a crash, putting the occupants at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag warning light on the dashboard
airbag system failure to detect occupants
airbag disabled warning
refusal of warranty coverage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress can cause electrical issues, leading to stalling, failure to start, and potential fires. This can be dangerous, especially when driving, and can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Water sloshing around inside the car frame
water gushing into the passenger floorboard from behind the dashboard
damp seats
and difficulty starting or shutting off the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden stalling can cause accidents, especially when driving on busy roads or highways. This can be dangerous and lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The car shuts off without warning
no signs of stalling or sputtering before shutting off
and difficulty restarting the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause jerking or stalling, leading to loss of control and potential accidents. This can be dangerous, especially when driving on busy roads or highways.
symptoms: Intermittent jerking of the car between 1000-2000 RPM
transmission skipping a beat
and sudden slowing down or propelling forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Weak frame and structural integrity can lead to excessive damage in minor accidents, resulting in total loss of the vehicle. This can be a safety concern and lead to financial losses.
symptoms: Excessive damage to the frame
engine
and surrounding components in minor accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Omissions of safety features, such as backup cameras, and potential recalls of mechanical key systems can lead to safety concerns and potential accidents.
symptoms: Lack of backup camera
mechanical key system failure
and potential recalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can lead to engine failure, fires, and potential accidents. This can be a safety concern and lead to financial losses.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the engine area
seepage or leaking oil
and potential engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose acceleration, or experience harsh shifting, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shudders
slips gears
revs at high RPM
has a loud whine coming from the transmission
has a slipping feeling under hard acceleration
has a harsh downshift
slow speed shutter
and bump when coming to a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch assembly can cause the clutch pedal to stick, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the clutch gets released but the gear is still in the previous gear
getting into reverse is not easy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission range sensor can cause the vehicle to slip gears, rev at high RPM, and lose acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine lamp light comes on
the vehicle begins to slip gears
revs at high RPM
and has a risk of stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Transparency and Accountability from Nissan Dealerships and Corporation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of transparency and accountability from Nissan dealerships and corporation can lead to frustrated customers, delayed or denied repairs, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Dealerships claim to repair components without providing clear documentation
dealerships fail to diagnose problems
dealerships blame the customer's driving habits
Nissan corporation refuses to acknowledge and address widespread transmission issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical issues with the ignition can cause the vehicle to stall, increasing the risk of a crash or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the ignition switch moves out of the run position to the accessory position
turning off the engine
the key fails to release from the ignition switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of a standard backup camera or malfunctioning backup camera can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: No backup camera is available on lower trim levels
the backup camera display settings can be adjusted to make the rear view image no longer visible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brake lights can increase the risk of a crash, and the sudden depression of the brake pedal can cause loss of control.
symptoms: The brake lights intermittently go out
the brakes suddenly depress even more while the vehicle is in drive and the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, increasing the risk of a crash or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel pump needs to be replaced frequently
in this case
twice with only 60k miles on the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning check engine warning light can lead to delayed diagnosis and repair of underlying issues, potentially causing further damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The check engine warning light is illuminated on the instrument panel
but the vehicle was not repaired.
